OL,3,CGovernment unveils 'bus revolution' to
OL,4,Cgive local authorities more control
OL,6,FThis model ` known as bus franchising
OL,7,F` involves local authorities granting
OL,8,Fprivate companies the right to operate
OL,9,Fin a specific area but retaining
OL,10,Fcontrol over key aspects of the
OL,11,Fservice such as routes, timetables and
OL,12,Ffares.
OL,14,FThe Department for Transport (DfT)
OL,15,Fplans to bring forward a Buses Bill
OL,16,Flater in this parliamentary session to
OL,17,Fdeliver changes to further support
OL,18,Ffranchising, alongside other measures
OL,19,Fon areas such as funding and
OL,20,Faccessible travel.
